{
  "texts": [
    "Recent advancements in Large Language Models (LLMs), particularly OpenAI's Generative Pre-trained Transformers (GPT), have paved the way for integrating LLM-powered chatbots into interactive textbooks to enhance the learning experience for engineering students.",
    "LLM-based applications can form an integral part of the teaching resources available to students, and their natural language interface makes them ideal for supplementing and supporting the in-person teaching team.",
    "However, setting up and using an LLM-based application remains a nontrivial task.Despite their world knowledge and ability to answer many questions factually, LLMs can suffer from hallucinations, in which they present plausible but incorrect information as though it were fact [1].",
    "Regardless of hallucinations, a pre-trained LLM will not have specific knowledge about the course it is being used for.",
    "It may be able to provide useful, general information, but it will not know the nuances of the course."
  ]
}